    • getPedigrees

      public static Map<String,Pedigree> getPedigrees()
      Returns the mapping from individual ID to a record in the pedigrees file. Available field names in the record are: "Family ID", "Individual ID", "Paternal ID", "Maternal ID", "Gender", "Phenotype", "Population", "Relationship", "Siblings", "Second Order", "Third Order", "Children", "Other Comments"

    • getSample

      public static Set<Region> getSample(Phase1KG phase)
      Get the Set of Region for the given phase. The people contained in these regions (and the list of regions and zones) are loaded from the resource files

    • getPhases

      public static Set<Phase1KG> getPhases()
      Gets the list of phases declared in the resource file sample/phaseList.txt
      This included unsupported ones.
      See also isSupported(Phase1KG)

    • isSupported

      public static boolean isSupported(Phase1KG phase)
      Check if the given phase is currently supported.
      To support a new phase, add a new phase file in the sample resource folder, and declare it in the samples/phaseList.txt file

    • getVcfUrlTemplate

      public static String getVcfUrlTemplate(Phase1KG phase1KG)
      Gets the VCF URL template for the selected phase

    • getChrEndPosition

      public static Optional<Integer> getChrEndPosition(HumanGenomeVersions hgVersion, String chrName)
      Gets the end position for the given chromosome
      Parameters:
      hgVersion - the human genome version
      chrName - the name of the chromosome. `1` for example.
      Returns:
      the end position (empty if chromosome not found in the file, or if an error occurred while reading the file)
